sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant X as Apex<br/>(GoogleCalendarService)
    participant C as Salesforce Certificate<br/>"GoogleSA" (private key)
    participant T as Google Token Endpoint<br/>oauth2.googleapis.com/token
    participant G as Google Calendar API<br/>www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3

    X->>X: Auth.JWT — write the claims:<br/>iss = service account email<br/>scope = calendar.events<br/>aud = the token endpoint
    X->>C: Auth.JWS — sign it (RS256)<br/>private key never leaves Salesforce
    C-->>X: signed JWT (sealed letter)
    X->>T: Auth.JWTBearerTokenExchange<br/>grant_type=…jwt-bearer&amp;assertion=&lt;JWT&gt;
    T-->>X: access_token (Bearer, ~1 hour)
    X->>G: POST /calendars/{calendarId}/events (create)<br/>GET · PATCH · DELETE /events/{eventId}
    G-->>X: 2xx + event JSON (id, htmlLink…)

    Note over X,G: Same sealed-letter recipe as the inbound lab —<br/>this time Google is the castle checking the seal
